Critical assumptions and Constraints
A main constraint is time and budget.  Time available is 6 weeks and there is no budget.
Our critical assumptions include the assumption that someone will edit/maintain the site for certain features like the calendar and update section.  Another assumption is that people will be able to find the site. 

Analysis of Option and Recommendation
Wordpress is better for our time and cost constraints.  Wordpress is free to host.  A downside to wordpress is that it is less unique.  Making a site from scratch using html would exceed time and cost limitations.  Dreamweaver would push the boundaries of time constraints and exceeds cost limitations.
Other club sites use wordpress probably due to itâ€™s user-friendliness and low cost.

1.0  Introduction/Background â€“ The Brazilian Jiu Jitsu club is a newly formed club at UCI, which started in spring of last year. It was founded by AJ Albert to help promote collegiate level competitions between universities within California. The goal of the club is to help further the cause of spreading Brazilian Jiu Jitsu and to allow for affordable competitions for students of Universities. In doing this the art and sport of Brazilian Jiu Jitsu is being promoted and helps both the members of the club and the community at large by introducing those who may not have been exposed to the sport before get a chance to try it out if they are interested in doing so.
2.0   Business Objective â€“ The objective of this project is to create a website that will be available and easy to access by the general public where new and interested parties may be referred to in which to find out more about the Brazilian Jiu Jitsu club. This also will incorporate current members looking to keep up to date with the club events, and even provide a place for club photos as well as a simple Q&A about how to join the Brazilian Jiu Jitsu club. The overall objective is to increase membership and publicity of the club, bringing in as many members as would like to join, from the complete novices to the experienced practitioners of the sport. This website should be easily referenced by current members to new ones in order for them to have their questions asked, and for current members to find the information and media that they so wish to find out about current events or posts within the club, including a list of the current members and officers, and their belt ranks.
3.0  Current Situation and Problem/Opportunity Statement â€“ The current state of the Brazilian Jiu Jitsu club is that there is no current website that functions solely for the purposes of the club, but rather there is a stub on the UCI club pages, and a Facebook page for UCI Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, which acts as a message board and information hub for both the ARC class that is being offered and the UCI Brazilian Jiu Jitsu club. The problem is that the class and the club are two separate entities, whereas anyone who has a membership at the ARC can join the class, only either undergraduate or graduate students can join the club. Another problem that arises is that there isnâ€™t much information given about the club on the Facebook page, thus people who are looking for the club have nowhere else to turn. This provides the opportunity to give interested people a place to look up information on how to join the club and where/when they meet. Other information being provided on the site will help promote the club and show past events, list future events, and show the current weekly schedule, as well as a multitude of resources for those interested in Brazilian Jiu Jitsu in general.

6.0 Preliminary Project Requirements

The main features of the Brazilian Jiu-jitsu club website include the following:

1. The ability for administrators to easily update the website with new content and make changes as necessary.

2. Club members should be able to search for the website easily via search engines.

3. Appropriate security measures to permit access to the entire website to the administrators and certain sections of the website to regular as well as new users alike.

4. Access to all the major aspects of the website including club history, calendars, updates and the like.

7.0 Budget Estimate and Financial Analysis

In terms of an estimated cost for this type of website, it is not necessary to invest money into developing what will most likely just be a small scale website that simply serves to keep the members of the Brazilian Jiu-jitsu club informed about the latest developments. The only factor that would be taken into consideration is the number of hours that would need to be invested in order to meet the given deadline.

8.0 Schedule Estimate

The sponsor would like to see the website polished and up and running in less than eight weeks. Approximately 6-7 weeks will be devoted to creating and polishing the website and provided that everything is handled accordingly, the remaining time will be spent fixing any bugs or other issues that may hinder the website in some fashion.

The website will feature information on the sport of Jiu Jitsu, history of the sport and a Q&A section on joining the club.  The second objective will be to allow current members to stay connected to the club by providing up to date information on club events, tournament dates, list of club memebers and officers, member belt ranks and other pertinent information.
